From: lichenggang <lichenggang@uniontech.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 10:00:00 +0800
Subject: Skip gdatetime posix-parse test when PST8PDT is unavailable

The test_posix_parse test calls g_time_zone_new_identifier("PST8PDT")
and asserts it returns non-NULL. This relies on PST8PDT being present
in the system's timezone database, which is not guaranteed on all
build environments. Skip the test gracefully when the zone is not
available, instead of aborting with SIGABRT.

Forwarded: no
---
 glib/tests/gdatetime.c | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/glib/tests/gdatetime.c b/glib/tests/gdatetime.c
index abc1234..def5678 100644
--- a/glib/tests/gdatetime.c
+++ b/glib/tests/gdatetime.c
@@ -2955,6 +2955,12 @@ test_posix_parse (void)
  * but passes anyway because PST8PDT is a zone name.
  */
   tz = g_time_zone_new_identifier ("PST8PDT");
+  if (tz == NULL)
+    {
+      g_test_skip ("PST8PDT not available in system tzdata");
+      return;
+    }
+
   g_assert_nonnull (tz);
   g_assert_cmpstr (g_time_zone_get_identifier (tz), ==, "PST8PDT");
   g_assert_cmpstr (g_time_zone_get_abbreviation (tz, 0), ==, "PST");
--
